<p>For a more detailed analysis of the changes of the Li and Al atomic positions, we calculated the partial coordination numbers (PCNs), 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm20">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>N</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mi>i</mi>
       <mi>j</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, which give the average number of 
 <italic>j</italic>-type atoms within the cut-off distance, 
 <italic>R</italic>
 <sub>cut</sub>, of an 
 <italic>i</italic>-type atom from the PDF according to:
 <disp-formula id="FD2-molecules-24-02667">
  <label>(2)</label>
  <math id="mm21">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>N</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mi>i</mi>
       <mi>j</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <msubsup>
      <mstyle mathsize="140%" displaystyle="true">
       <mo>∫</mo>
      </mstyle>
      <mn>0</mn>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>R</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mi>c</mi>
         <mi>u</mi>
         <mi>t</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </msubsup>
     <mn>4</mn>
     <mi>π</mi>
     <msup>
      <mi>r</mi>
      <mn>2</mn>
     </msup>
     <mi>ρ</mi>
     <msub>
      <mi>g</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mi>i</mi>
       <mi>j</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mi>r</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mi>d</mi>
     <mi>r</mi>
     <mo>,</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm22">
   <mrow>
    <mi>ρ</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the number density [
 <xref rid="B26-molecules-24-02667" ref-type="bibr">26</xref>,
 <xref rid="B27-molecules-24-02667" ref-type="bibr">27</xref>]. The cut-off distance, 
 <italic>R
  <sub>cut</sub>
 </italic>, was selected to be the distance corresponding to the tail of the first peak in the PDF.
</p>
